posts.raw_content:
If you can't code but want to cold contact the company for an H1B job, post the job title that you are interested in and qualified for, and I will post the case number, job title/soc title and contact email address in the reply.

If you want to do this too, I can send you my python code.  It's not great but it will do the job.

Python script:

import pandas as pd

df = pd.read_excel("https://www.dol.gov/sites/dolgov/files/ETA/oflc/pdfs/LCA_Disclosure_Data_FY2025_Q3.xlsx") #download the Excel file from dol, remember to change the filename for future quarters

df1 = df[df['CASE_STATUS'].str.lower() == 'certified'] #filter the dataset to only certified cases 

job_title = ['security engineer', 'Engineers/Architects'] #update job_title to positions you are qualified for. You can use multiple keywords, it will pull all jobs that contain those words

JobTitle = '|'.join(job_title)

mask = (
    df1['JOB_TITLE'].str.contains(JobTitle, case=False, na=False) |
    df1['SOC_TITLE'].str.contains(JobTitle, case=False, na=False)
)

df2 = df1[mask]

df3 = df2[['CASE_NUMBER','JOB_TITLE', 'SOC_TITLE', 'EMPLOYER_POC_EMAIL']].reset_index(drop = True) #job title and employer point of contact email address

print(df3)

"""
You can email the company using your personal email or
write another script to mass emails all companies at once
"""
